text: Chantalle Zijderveld (born 17 September 2000) is a Dutch swimmer. She competed in S10 classification freestyle events, but her specialty is the SB9 breaststroke, taking two European and one World title in the 100m distance. ==Personal history== Zijderveld was born in Zwijndrecht, Netherlands in 2000. She was born without a right hand. ==International career== Zijderveld made her international debut in 2013, during the World Championships in Montréal. == References == Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch female swimmers Category:S10-classified Paralympic swimmers Category:Medalists at the World Para Swimming Championships Category:Medalists at the World Para Swimming European Championships Category:Sportspeople from Zwijndrecht, Netherlands Category:Paralympic medalists in swimming Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for the Netherlands Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Paralympics Category:Swimmers at the 2016 Summer Paralympics Category:Paralympic swimmers of the Netherlands
